The Anambra State Police command has arrested a couple that conspired to sell their son for the sum of N300, 000. In a statement issued to newsmen in Akwa on Saturday by the State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Haruna Mohammed, the couple were arrested at about 2: pm on Tuesday. The couple Chinonso Anyanwu, 32, and his wife, Oluebube, 20, are from lbiasiegbe in Imo State. The police spokesman said they conspired to sell their baby boy to  one Sandra Odimege of Umuezike, Amorka of Ihiala  Local Government Area  of Anambra State.  Police nap couple who sold baby for N300,000 Baby factory: Police smash syndicate 64 year-old carjacker, two others arrested in Anambra Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin